<div class='panel'><h2>How does it works ?</h2><br>

<p>When you create an account on Mastodon, you create an account on the website you currently are visiting. For example, here you are on <a href="https://pegelinux.ga">pegelinux.ga</a>. That is your instance. <br>

You will notice after log in two different timelines, the Local and the Federated.
The local timeline is all the public toots of all our local users ( the one who registered on <a href="https://pegelinux.ga">pegelinux.ga</a> and use it to access the Mastodon federation ).
The federated timeline adds the public toots of all the users that our local users are following in other servers.</p><br>


<h2>How do I get verified ? Who is who ?</h2><br>

<p>Do it yourself ;) For now there is no verification on Mastodon, it's just an emoji that people add as a joke.
